<subSubSection id="C37A73B1FFA1FFC401A71518FE1DF844" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDF203AFFA1FFC401A71518FE1DF844" blockId="115.[151,1436,1906,2041]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA1FFC401A71518FE91F831" bold="true" box="[151,274,1906,1932]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(Emended) Prostomium elongate, pointed; eyespots present or absent; peristomium with two rings, variously developed; body regions separated into thorax and abdomen; branchiae present from abdominal segments; all parapodia with camerated capillaries; acicular spines or uncini present in thoracic neuropodia; pygidium with dorsal anus and 2–4 anal cirri.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A73B1FFA6FFC301F712FDFC68FF68" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF203AFFA6FFC301F712FDFC68FF68" blockId="116.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC301F712FDFECBFF0C" bold="true" box="[199,328,151,177]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC3006A12FDFDA8FF0C" box="[346,555,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Gesaschroederella</emphasis>
is formed by adding the first name to the surname of Dr. 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC305D012FDFA9BFF0C" authorityName="Hartmann" authorityYear="1957" box="[1248,1304,151,177]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Gesa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="116" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gesa</taxonomicName>
Hartmann- Schr̂der, for whom the late Dr. Lucien Laubier originally named the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A73B1FFA6FFC301F712B5FE02FDA4" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDF203AFFA6FFC301F712B5FEC9FE10" blockId="116.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC301F712B5FEB7FF44" bold="true" box="[199,308,223,249]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Remarks</emphasis>
. As reported in this study, juveniles of several species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC302E312B5FBF5FF44" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1977" box="[979,1142,223,249]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC302E312B5FBF5FF44" box="[979,1142,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC3058212B5FA9CFF44" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1828" box="[1202,1311,223,249]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Scoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC3058212B5FA9CFF44" box="[1202,1311,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Scoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been found with characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC300D41369FDFCFEA0" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1921" box="[484,639,259,285]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Schroederella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC300D41369FDFCFEA0" box="[484,639,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Schroederella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by Laubier (1962, 1971), here renamed 
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC305FB1369FA1FFEA0" box="[1227,1436,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Gesaschroederella</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC301A7134DFE98FEFC" bold="true" box="[151,283,295,321]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">nomen nov</emphasis>
. The use of fine-mesh sieves permits the collection of juvenile orbiniids that were previously not available from surveys of benthic invertebrates. Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC3038E1321FCB3FED8" authorityName="Laubier" authorityYear="1962" box="[702,816,331,357]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Schroederella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="paulini">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC3038E1321FCB3FED8" box="[702,816,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">G. paulini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC302571321FC60FED8" baseAuthorityName="Badalamenti &amp; Castella" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[871,995,331,357]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Gesa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laubieri">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC302571321FC60FED8" box="[871,995,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">G. laubieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be compared with local species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC301861305FEA0FE34" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1828" box="[182,291,367,393]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Scoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC301861305FEA0FE34" box="[182,291,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Scoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F37760AAFFA6FFC300581305FE74FE34" box="[360,503,367,393]" name="South Africa" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and the Mediterranean Sea to explore the possibility that they are also juveniles of larger orbiniids.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF203AFFA6FFC301F713DDFE02FDA4" blockId="116.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
Apart from being small and meiofaunal in habitat, there is nothing morphologically in the above definition except the presence of two peristomial rings that separates the two remaining species of 
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC305BC13B1FADEFE48" box="[1164,1373,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Gesaschroederella</emphasis>
from species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C605BB9FFA6FFC3003D1395FEF9FDA4" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1828" box="[269,378,511,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Scoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914FC28FFA6FFC3003D1395FEF9FDA4" box="[269,378,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Scoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
